			<h2><a href="http://www.dorkbot.org/dorkbotbristol/?p=68" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Project Neptune Light Up Dyrham Park">Project Neptune Light Up Dyrham Park</a></h2>
			<h4>October 22nd, 2007<!-- by Clare --> &middot; <a href="http://www.dorkbot.org/dorkbotbristol/?p=68#respond" title="Comment on Project Neptune Light Up Dyrham Park">No Comments</a></h4>
			<div class="entry">
				<p>On 26th October 2007, <a href="http://www.projectneptune.co.uk/" onclick="javascript:urchinTracker('/outbound/www.projectneptune.co.uk/?ref=/dorkbotbristol/index.php?paged=4');">Project Neptune</a> will recreate the grandeur of Dyrham Park’s lost gardens through a compelling combination of pyrotechnic effects, lighting, video-projections, performance and sound. Young people from Monks Park School Bristol and a crack team of experienced arts professionals will stage a spectacular outdoor event at a late 17th century mansion near Bath, managed by the The National Trust.</p>
<p>Project Neptune seeks to interest young people in heritage. It is staged in association with artist Nathan Hughes and Dyrham Park’s Education Department.</p>
<p>Read more at <a href="http://www.projectneptune.co.uk/" onclick="javascript:urchinTracker('/outbound/www.projectneptune.co.uk/?ref=/dorkbotbristol/index.php?paged=4');">www.projectneptune.co.uk</a></p>
